CFTC's Gensler: Client Fund Segregation 'Heart' of Derivatives Regulation
The model of walling off customer money from that of big derivatives brokers remains at the heart of U.S. regulation of the market, Commodity Futures Trading Commission Chairman Gary Gensler said Wednesday, despite charges that the practice failed customers of MF Global Holdings Ltd.
So-called segregation of customer funds, initiated in the 1930s for futures trade and last year backed by Congress for the off-exchange market in swaps, is the "heart of our regulatory regime," Mr. Gensler said at an event in Chicago...